{
  "texts": [
    "In the forward problem, the goal is to predict a response variable based on a model of predictor variables.",
    "For example, in y = a + b • x, y is the response variable, and x is the predictor variable with a and b constants.",
    "This can be simplified into a functional description as y = f (x, a, b).",
    "When focused on inverse problems, the goal is fundamentally different where we want to find the function f where y = f (x, a, b).",
    "That is, we are less concerned with how well our identified function f that maps (x, a, b) onto y fits, and more interested in which functions, if any, could do this."
  ]
}